= Teaching Statement

My goal as an educator is to make the powerful framework of economics accessible and applicable for every student while aligning with BI Norwegian Business School's dedication to impactful education and broad access. My teaching philosophy centers on clarity and experiential learning, principles that foster student-centric engagement and lifelong learning—a reflection of BI's commitment to continuous improvement and positive societal impact.

I strive to translate complex economic theories into clear, intuitive language, bridging the gap between formal theoretical constructs and students’ real-world understanding. This bilingual approach enables students from diverse backgrounds to build a strong conceptual foundation, enhancing accessibility in line with BI’s value of empowering individuals regardless of background.

Equally important is active involvement with economic principles. By integrating hands-on workshops and guided problem-solving sessions, I transform abstract concepts into practical tools, preparing students for applied economics careers that the Economics Department prioritizes. This method resonates with BI’s strategy of fostering innovation and relevance within an international context.

In my teaching, students are partners in a dynamic learning process, where mistakes are opportunities and guidance is personalized. Feedback has underscored the supportive environment I cultivate—encouraging curiosity and confidence in analyzing complex issues. This pedagogical approach aligns with the department’s research-based and experience-based teaching ethos.

Ultimately, my ambition is to empower students with economics as a toolkit to critically engage with the world, supporting BI’s mission of creating positive societal impact through education and research. I look forward to contributing to BI’s vibrant academic community, collaborating with faculty who combine rigorous research with practical applications, and advancing knowledge that reflects Nordic values and global relevance.
